(60,'== Installation ==\n* \'\'\'Prepare Server\'\'\' (10.21.54.77)\n# Update server: yum update -y\n# Install JDK8 from Oracle or OpenJDK: \n#:Download java-1.8.0-openjdk-1.8.0.242.b08-0.el7_7.x86_64.rpm\n#:rpm -ivh java-1.8.0-openjdk-1.8.0.242.b08-0.el7_7.x86_64.rpm\n# Install Jenkins binary\n#:Download jenkins-2.221-1.1.noarch.rpm \n#:rpm -ivh jenkins-2.221-1.1.noarch.rpm\n* \'\'\'Configure Jenkins\'\'\'\n#:Edit /etc/sysconfig/jenkins and optimize parameters with ports, Java memory, Jenkins Home etc.\n#:Download appropriate war file and put it in /usr/lib/jenkins/\n# Configure Linux Firewalld service\n#:Allow ports 8080 & 44111 in Firewalld for communications between master and slaves.\n#:We can also use SSH credentials for master-slave communication.\n# We are using NginX proxy for access jenkins by DNS (devops.rril.ril.com)\n#:Configure a virtual host in our niginx proxy server (10.21.58.25) and restart nginx service\n#:Now Jenkins Dashboard is accessible by browser https://devops.rril.ril.com\n#:[[File:Jenkins.png|frame|none|Jenkins]]\n\n* \'\'\'Pipeline\'\'\'\n#Create a New Item\n#:We are choosing here Pipeline\n#:[[File:Pipe.png|frame|none|Pipeline]]\n#After giving a project name, we need to write groovy code for pipeline.\n#This pipeline code is a combination of multiple stages.\n#For Retail IT we are making following stages\n#::Stage1: SCM Checkout\n#::Stage2: Build and Test with Dev branch\n#::Stage3: Unit test (Depend of automated test scripts)\n#::Stage4: If successful, merge code to master branch and update Gitlab\n#::Stage5: Sonar Qube analysis for code\n#::Stage6: Fortify Test:Code are pushed to Fortify server for vulnerability check\n#::Stage7: After successful test, build the application with the master branch\n#::Stage8: Build Docker Image and pushed image to private Docker repository (docker.rril.ril.com)\n#::Stage9: Deploy:This is the CD part in this pipeline. Docker image is pulled to specified node and run.\n* \'\'\'<u>Stage View</u>\'\'\'\n[[File:StageView.png|frame|none|StageView]]\n\n* \'\'\'<u>BlueOcean View</u>\'\'\'\n[[File:BlueOcean.png|border|1000px|BlueOcean View]]','utf-8'),
(61,'\'\'\'Ingress Controller\'\'\'\n\n\'\'\' <u>This is required to load balancing between services inside pods</u>\'\'\'\n\n# Download configuration files for installation\n#:- git clone http://git.rril.ril.com/Retail-Devops/kubernetes-ingress.git \'\'\'OR\'\'\'\n#:- git clone https://github.com/nginxinc/kubernetes-ingress.git\n# <code>cd kubernetes-ingress/deployments</code>\n#:- kubectl apply -f common/ns-and-sa.yaml\n#:- kubectl apply -f rbac/rbac.yaml\n#:- kubectl apply -f common/default-server-secret.yaml\n#:- kubectl apply -f common/nginx-config.yaml\n#:- kubectl apply -f common/custom-resource-definitions.yaml\n#:- kubectl apply -f daemon-set/nginx-ingress.yaml\n# Now you can check for the controller\n#:- kubectl get pod -n nginx-ingress\n# Youcan also follow the documentation at:\n#:<code>https://docs.nginx.com/nginx-ingress-controller/installation/</code>','utf-8'),
