(230,'* \'\'\'A very simple method of Nodewise deployment depends on Namespaces\'\'\'\n\n<pre>\nEdit /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-apiserver.yaml\n\nAdd PodNodeSelector in this line\n--enable-admission-plugins=NodeRestriction\nTO\n--enable-admission-plugins=NodeRestriction,PodNodeSelector\n</pre>\n\'\'\'<u>Once this file is updated, cluster will be restart automatically</u>\'\'\'\n\n\'\'\'Now need to add Label and Environments to all the nodes\'\'\'\n<pre>kubectl label node <node_name> env=web\nkubectl label node <node_name> env=back</pre>\n\n\'\'\'Now edit Namespaces\'\'\'\n<pre>kubectl edit ns <ns_name>\nAdd Annotations as:\n  annotations:\n    scheduler.alpha.kubernetes.io/node-selector: env=web </pre>\n\n\'\'\'Now edit Nodes\'\'\'\n<pre>kubectl edit node <NodeName>\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    ----\n    ----\n    env: <web/dmz/ndmz/etc.> </pre>\n\n\'\'\'Now you can deploy Nodewise deployment depends on Namespaces\'\'\'','utf-8'),
