(268,'*<u>\'\'\'Install and configure Elasticsearch\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>\nDownload Elasticsearch\nwget https://artifacts.elastic.co/downloads/elasticsearch/elasticsearch-7.13.2-x86_64.rpm\nyum localinstall elasticsearch-7.13.2-x86_64.rpm -y </pre>\n\n*<u>\'\'\'Configure Elasticsearch\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>Edit configuration file with respective parameters:\n/etc/elasticsearch/elasticsearch.yml</pre>\n\n*<u>\'\'\'X-Pack Security\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>In default settings, X-Pack security is disable. To enable this, followings are the steps.\n* Create SSL certificate for Elasticsearch and enable SSL\n# cd /etc/elasticsearch/\n# /usr/share/elasticsearch/bin/elasticsearch-certutil ca</pre>\n<pre>Press Enter for all (With blank password for certificate)</pre>\n\n[[File:Ca-certs.png|frame|none]]\n\n[[File:Certs.png|frame|none]]\n\n[[File:Complete-certs.png|frame|none]]\n\n*<u>\'\'\'Update elasticsearch.yml\'\'\'</u>\n[[File:A2.png|frame|none]]\n*<u>\'\'\'Generate elasticsearch credentials\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>#/usr/share/elasticsearch/bin/elasticsearch-setup-passwords auto\nCopy all credentials.</pre>\n\n*<u>\'\'\'Start Elasticsearch\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>systemctl start elasticsearch</pre>\n\n*<u>\'\'\'Install Grafana Server\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>\nFor Retail IT, Grafana & Kibana server is installed in 10.129.36.230\n\nDownload Grafana server:\nwget https://dl.grafana.com/oss/release/grafana-8.0.3-1.x86_64.rpm\nyum localinstall grafana-8.0.3-1.x86_64.rpm -y\n</pre>\n*<u>\'\'\'Configure Grafana Server\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>\nEdit file with specified parameters:\n/etc/grafana/grafana.ini\n\nIf you are using proxy server to access Grafana Dashboard, need to configure root_url as\nroot_url = %(protocol)s://%(domain)s:%(http_port)s/grafana/\n</pre>\n*<u>\'\'\'Start Grafana Server\'\'\'</u>\n<pre>\nsystemctl start grafana-server\n\nNow Grafana Dashboard is accessible via default port number 3000.\nIf you configured proxy, then can be accessible as https://<domain.com>/grafana/\n</pre>','utf-8'),
