(299,'=== InfluxDB with Telegraf is a better option for monitoring System Metrics with Alert ===\n\'\'\'Download InfluxDB\'\'\'\n<pre>wget https://dl.influxdata.com/influxdb/releases/influxdb-1.8.6.x86_64.rpm\n\nyum localinstall -y influxdb-1.8.6.x86_64.rpm</pre>\n\'\'\'Configure InfluxDB\'\'\'\n<pre>Check configuration file for any required change\n/etc/influxdb/influxdb.conf\n\nStart influxDB\nsystemctl start influxdb\nsystemctl enable influxdb\n\nLogin to DB console\n$ influx\nConnected to http://localhost:8086 version 1.8.6\nInfluxDB shell version: 1.8.6\n> CREATE USER admin WITH PASSWORD \'<password>\' WITH ALL PRIVILEGES\n> CREATE USER grafana WITH PASSWORD \'<password>\' WITH ALL PRIVILEGES </pre>\n\'\'\'Download and configure Telegraf agent in each Nodes\'\'\'\n<pre>wget https://dl.influxdata.com/telegraf/releases/telegraf-1.19.1-1.x86_64.rpm\n\nConfigure:\nEdit configuration file /etc/telegraf/telegraf.conf</pre>\n<pre style=\"color: red;\">hostname = \"MY_HOST\" (Use this for customize host name)\n[[outputs.influxdb]]\n  urls = [\"http://<InfluxDB_IP>:8086\"] </pre>\n<pre>Start Telegraf:\nsystemctl start telegraf\nsystemctl enable telegraf</pre>','utf-8'),
