(312,'*\'\'\'Logstash configuration with 3 major blocks\'\'\'\n<pre>\nInput\nFilter\nOutput</pre>\n*<u>We can use variables for pattern of logs or Timestamp</u>\n\nFor Example logs:\n[[File:Log1.png|frame|none]]\n<pre>We need to segregate each part of the logs and define them by variables.\nThere are two parts in this log.\nOne is Timestamp and the other is Message\nWe can define the first part as a variable like BWTIME and write in a file.\nBWTIME %{YEAR} %{MONTH} %{MONTHDAY} %{TIME} GMT +%{INT}</pre>\nAnd complete message can be define as:\n[[File:Log2.png|frame|none]]\n\n<pre>Now we can make the complete config file as:</pre>\n\'\'\'Input Section\'\'\'\n<pre>\ninput {\n  file {\n        path => \"C:/path/to/the/logfile\"\n        start_position => \"beginning\"\n		codec => multiline {\n		patterns_dir => \"C:/path/to/the/pattern/directory\"\n		pattern => \"%{BWTIME} \"\n		negate => true\n		what => previous\n		}\n    }\n}</pre>\n\'\'\'Filter Section\'\'\'\n<pre>\nfilter{\n	grok{\n		patterns_dir => \"C:/logstash/config/Pattern/\"\n		match => { \"message\" => \"%{BWTIME:timestamp} %{DATA:application} *%{LOGLEVEL:LEVEL} \\[%{DATA:Error}] %{GREEDYDATA:log}\" }\n		remove_field => [\"message\"]\n	}\n}</pre>\n<pre style=\"color: red;\">Please do not copy past, without understand the log pattern, else it will be failed</pre>\n\'\'\'Output Section\'\'\'\n\n<i>Here we can choose, which Level of logs should push to elasticsearch / InfluxDB or and any othere consumer. In this example we are filtering only Error logs</i>\n<pre>\noutput {\nif [LEVEL] == \"Error\"\n{\n  stdout { codec =>  \"rubydebug\" }\n  elasticsearch {\n        hosts => [\"<Elastic_IP>:9200\"]\n        password => \"<Elastic_Password>\"\n        user => \"<Elastic_User>\"\n        index => \"<Index_Name>-%{+yyyy.MM.dd}\"\n  }\n }</pre>','utf-8'),
