(502,'*\'\'\'Edit /etc/haproxy/haproxy.cfg\'\'\'\n<pre>\nReplace with:\nlog /dev/log local0\n</pre>\n\n*\'\'\'Configure RSyslogd\'\'\'\n<pre>\nmkdir /var/lib/haproxy/dev\n\nCreate a new file:\n/etc/rsyslog.d/99-haproxy.conf\n\nAdd Following:\n$AddUnixListenSocket /var/lib/haproxy/dev/log\n#Send HAProxy messages to a dedicated logfile\n:programname, startswith, \"haproxy\" {\n/var/log/haproxy.log\nstop\n}</pre>\n\n*\'\'\'Restart services\'\'\'\n<pre>\nsystemctl daemon-reload\nsystemctl restart rsyslog.service\nsystemctl restart haproxy\n</pre>','utf-8'),
(503,'\n* \'\'\'Check and Update Kubernetes Certificate\'\'\'\n<pre>1. login to master server/control plane\n2. check certificate expiry using command: kubeadm alpha certs check-expiration\n3. renew certificates using command: kubeadm alpha certs renew all\n4. cp -i /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config\n5. systemctl daemon-reload\n6. systemctl restart docker\n7. systemctl restart kubelet\n8. setfacl --modify user:deploy:rw /var/run/docker.sock</pre>','utf-8'),
